                                                                                                                                    ITC to manage Parsvnath hotels

   OUR CORRESPONDENT
        Pradeep Jain

 Chairman, Parsvnath Developers
   
	New Delhi, Feb. 4: ITC Ltd will manage the hotels being set up by Parsvnath Developers. These hotels will be built over the next three to five years at an investment of Rs 2,500 crore.
 
	According to an agreement between Parsvnath Hotels, a subsidiary of Parsvnath Developers, and ITC, the latter will manage 50 hotels comprising 4,100 rooms across the country.
 
	While Parsvnath Hotels will own and develop these 50 properties, it will be managed by ITCs Fortune Park Hotels. Of these, 20 will be five-star hotels, 20 four-star and 10 three-star and budget hotels.
 
	At present, we are developing 17 hotels, of which seven will be managed by ITC. The remaining 10 will be managed by other hotel chains, said Pradeep Jain, chairman of Parsvnath Developers. 
 
	The seven hotels are in Ranchi, Lucknow, Indore, Jodhpur, Ujjain, Chandigarh and Dehradun. They are expected to be operational by 2010.
 
	Managing hotels requires expertise and we think Fortune Park is uniquely positioned to manage projects of different sizes and segments through its various brand extensions, he said.
 
	The hotels will be run under the brand name of Fortune Select, Fortune Park, Fortune Inn and Fortune Faith. Fortune Select hotels will have at least 100 rooms, Fortune Park 75 or more rooms and the other brands will have at least 50 rooms.
 
	Parsvnath plans to develop 75-100 hotels in Tier II, tier III and all the major cities across the country, he added.
 
	India is emerging as a preferred destination for tourists. Seeing this tremendous opportunity, we are venturing into the hospitality sector in a big way, Jain said.
 
	Parsvnath, the New Delhi-based real estate major, which recently entered the retail segment, is looking at Delhi, Pune, Mumbai, Calcutta and Chennai, to develop hotels in the near future. 
 
	ITC-Welcomgroup manages more than 80 hotels under different brands in India. The company has brands such as ITC Luxury Collection, Sheraton, Welcomhotel, Fortune Hotels and Welcome Heritage under its umbrella.
 
	Parsvnath Developers, which has presence in 48 cities and 17 states, has more than 100 real estate projects lined up with a land bank of 209 million sq ft. The company has posted a net profit of Rs 113 crore on a turnover of Rs 497 crore for the third quarter ended December 2007.
                                                            
